Assistant to the President for Counter-Terrorism and Homeland Security, John Brennan, called Yemeni President Ali Abdallah Saleh to discuss the importance of taking strong action against al-Qa'ida in the Arabian Peninsula (AQAP). They emphasized the need to enhance cooperation between Yemeni and U.S. counterterrorism and security services, as well as with other partner nations. Brennan also thanked President Saleh for his commitment to ensuring Yemen's full cooperation in combating al-Qa'ida and expressed appreciation for the sacrifices made by the Yemeni people.